00:43:34.579 --> 00:43:37.980
Look at Proverbs 14,

00:43:37.980 --> 00:43:39.980
but young ones especially have to beware,

00:43:39.980 --> 00:43:42.980
but there's no age restriction here.

00:43:42.980 --> 00:43:44.980
Verse 16,

00:43:44.980 --> 00:43:47.980
the wise one is cautious

00:43:47.980 --> 00:43:49.980
and turns away from evil.

00:43:49.980 --> 00:43:53.980
But the stupid one is reckless

00:43:53.980 --> 00:43:56.980
and overconfident.

00:43:56.980 --> 00:43:58.980
So, obviously, we don't want to be

00:43:58.980 --> 00:44:01.980
in the camp of the stupid one, do we?

00:44:01.980 --> 00:44:04.980
That one is reckless and overconfident.

00:44:04.980 --> 00:44:06.980
We want to be cautious

00:44:06.980 --> 00:44:08.980
and turn away from evil.

00:44:08.980 --> 00:44:10.980
Now, using this scripture as a foundation

00:44:10.980 --> 00:44:13.980
for our discussion, what are some cautions?

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:14.980
Because you know what it says,

00:44:14.980 --> 00:44:16.980
the wise one is cautious?

00:44:16.980 --> 00:44:18.980
What are some cautions that can help us

00:44:18.980 --> 00:44:21.980
from being, or keep us from being overconfident?

00:44:21.980 --> 00:44:23.980
Well, let's quickly discuss three.

00:44:23.980 --> 00:44:27.980
One, never overconfidently think

00:44:27.980 --> 00:44:31.980
we can take unauthorized liberties.

00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:33.980
Now, let's just talk about this for a moment.

00:44:33.980 --> 00:44:36.980
Here's two contrasting examples.

00:44:36.980 --> 00:44:38.980
Think of Aza.

00:44:38.980 --> 00:44:41.980
Now, no one knows to touch the arc of the covenant,

00:44:41.980 --> 00:44:43.980
but he reached out

00:44:43.980 --> 00:44:45.980
and grabbed hold of it, didn't he?

00:44:45.980 --> 00:44:47.980
Well, Jehovah struck him dead

00:44:47.980 --> 00:44:51.980
for this unauthorized liberty that he took.

00:44:51.980 --> 00:44:53.980
In contrast, think about David.

00:44:53.980 --> 00:44:56.980
Now, David, even though he had a perfect opportunity

00:44:56.980 --> 00:44:58.980
to kill Saul,

00:44:58.980 --> 00:45:01.980
his men were encouraging him to do it,

00:45:01.980 --> 00:45:06.980
he refused to touch the anointed of Jehovah.

00:45:06.980 --> 00:45:09.980
He even felt bad that he had disrespectfully touched

00:45:09.980 --> 00:45:12.980
the garments of the anointed of Jehovah.

00:45:12.980 --> 00:45:16.980
So he knew he had not been authorized to kill Saul.

00:45:16.980 --> 00:45:19.980
So he stayed in his place, he waited on Jehovah.

00:45:19.980 --> 00:45:21.980
And what a fine example for us.

00:45:21.980 --> 00:45:23.980
And I'm sure we can all think of,

00:45:23.980 --> 00:45:25.980
in regard to this first caution,

00:45:25.980 --> 00:45:28.980
we can think of application for here at Bethel

00:45:29.980 --> 00:45:32.980
in our congregation, even in our family.

00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:34.980
Let's get our second caution.

00:45:34.980 --> 00:45:40.980
Never overconfidently presume on Jehovah's mercy.

00:45:40.980 --> 00:45:42.980
Now, let's think about this.

00:45:42.980 --> 00:45:46.980
An example of this could be ones that think

00:45:46.980 --> 00:45:49.980
they'll leave the truth for a while.

00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:52.980
They'll have some fun in this world.

00:45:52.980 --> 00:45:56.980
They'll enjoy some selfish desires

00:45:56.980 --> 00:45:58.980
and then they'll come back later to Jehovah.

00:45:58.980 --> 00:46:01.980
And Jehovah will take them back to Jehovah will forgive them.

00:46:01.980 --> 00:46:03.980
But now, isn't that very risky?

00:46:03.980 --> 00:46:06.980
Isn't that a reckless course?

00:46:06.980 --> 00:46:10.980
In fact, it makes me think of the story of the dog

00:46:10.980 --> 00:46:14.980
we had on the farm when I was about 11 or 12 years old.

00:46:14.980 --> 00:46:15.980
He was a good dog.

00:46:15.980 --> 00:46:17.980
We loved him. His name was Wheeler.

00:46:17.980 --> 00:46:19.980
But one night,

00:46:19.980 --> 00:46:22.980
there was a pack of wild dogs that came through the valley

00:46:22.980 --> 00:46:23.980
where we lived.

00:46:24.980 --> 00:46:28.980
And Wheeler took off with these wild dogs.

00:46:28.980 --> 00:46:29.980
Now, we couldn't understand it

00:46:29.980 --> 00:46:31.980
because we took such good care of him.

00:46:31.980 --> 00:46:32.980
I asked Dad, why?

00:46:32.980 --> 00:46:34.980
Why would he do that?

00:46:34.980 --> 00:46:35.980
Well, my father said,

00:46:35.980 --> 00:46:38.980
maybe there's a female in the pack.

00:46:38.980 --> 00:46:40.980
Maybe he just wants to have fun for a while,

00:46:40.980 --> 00:46:42.980
but I'm pretty sure he'll come home.

00:46:42.980 --> 00:46:45.980
Well, he did come home about a week later.

00:46:45.980 --> 00:46:46.980
But he was all chewed up.

00:46:46.980 --> 00:46:48.980
He had been in a horrible fight

00:46:48.980 --> 00:46:51.980
with one or more of the other dogs apparently in the pack.

00:46:51.980 --> 00:46:54.980
And he barely made it back to his doghouse.

00:46:54.980 --> 00:46:56.980
It took him a couple of weeks.

00:46:56.980 --> 00:46:57.980
He slowly recovered.

00:46:57.980 --> 00:47:00.980
He never had this same strength that he had previously.

00:47:00.980 --> 00:47:02.980
But now, here's a really sad part of the story.

00:47:02.980 --> 00:47:03.980
About two years later,

00:47:03.980 --> 00:47:06.980
another pack of wild dogs came through.

00:47:06.980 --> 00:47:09.980
And again, he ran off with them.

00:47:09.980 --> 00:47:11.980
Now, we couldn't believe it.

00:47:11.980 --> 00:47:13.980
This time, he came back,

00:47:13.980 --> 00:47:15.980
even he was gone longer.

00:47:15.980 --> 00:47:18.980
And he couldn't even make it back this time to the doghouse.

00:47:18.980 --> 00:47:20.980
We found him the next morning in the yard

00:47:20.980 --> 00:47:25.980
and my brother and I gently carried him to his doghouse

00:47:25.980 --> 00:47:29.980
and about a day later he died in that doghouse.

00:47:29.980 --> 00:47:30.980
Now, we cried.

00:47:30.980 --> 00:47:31.980
We couldn't believe it.

00:47:31.980 --> 00:47:33.980
Now, he was just a dog.

00:47:33.980 --> 00:47:35.980
But if you think about that story,

00:47:35.980 --> 00:47:38.980
some of our young ones really remind you

00:47:38.980 --> 00:47:41.980
of that dog, Wheeler.

00:47:41.980 --> 00:47:44.980
They're so well cared for by those that love them,

00:47:44.980 --> 00:47:45.980
especially Jehovah,

00:47:45.980 --> 00:47:48.980
but they think they're missing out on fun.

00:47:48.980 --> 00:47:51.980
And so they will run with the world for a while,

00:47:51.980 --> 00:47:53.980
thinking probably in the back of their head,

00:47:53.980 --> 00:47:55.980
they're going to come back to the truth later.

00:47:55.980 --> 00:47:57.980
But how foolish, how recklessly

00:47:57.980 --> 00:48:00.980
may none of us even slightly think this way

00:48:00.980 --> 00:48:01.980
and may we help others,

00:48:01.980 --> 00:48:03.980
and especially our young ones,

00:48:03.980 --> 00:48:06.980
to never foolishly reason this way.

00:48:06.980 --> 00:48:09.980
But one more caution, a third,

00:48:09.980 --> 00:48:13.980
never overconfidently rely on ourselves.

00:48:13.980 --> 00:48:16.980
Solomon, apparently, that was his downfall.

00:48:16.980 --> 00:48:21.980
He knew he was not to increase the number of horses,

00:48:21.980 --> 00:48:23.980
increase wives.

00:48:23.980 --> 00:48:25.980
See, he was not ignorant.

00:48:25.980 --> 00:48:28.980
He knew, but somehow he must have rationalized.

00:48:28.980 --> 00:48:29.980
He was an exception.

00:48:29.980 --> 00:48:30.980
See, he was strong enough.

00:48:30.980 --> 00:48:31.980
He was wise enough.

00:48:31.980 --> 00:48:32.980
He could handle it.

00:48:32.980 --> 00:48:36.980
Well, that was the pride before the crash, wasn't it?

00:48:36.980 --> 00:48:37.980
Or what about Peter?

00:48:37.980 --> 00:48:39.980
Apparently his downfall.

00:48:39.980 --> 00:48:41.980
In effect, he said,

00:48:41.980 --> 00:48:43.980
all the others may have weaknesses in their faith,

00:48:43.980 --> 00:48:45.980
but not me, Lord.

00:48:45.980 --> 00:48:47.980
I'll never fail you.

00:48:47.980 --> 00:48:50.980
But this overconfident, self-reliant,

00:48:50.980 --> 00:48:52.980
I am more faithful than they are attitude,

00:48:52.980 --> 00:48:55.980
was followed by a terrible crash.

00:48:55.980 --> 00:48:58.980
And that makes us think of Paul's words

00:48:58.980 --> 00:49:00.980
at 2 Corinthians 1210,

00:49:00.980 --> 00:49:02.980
when I am weak,

00:49:02.980 --> 00:49:03.980
then I am powerful.

00:49:03.980 --> 00:49:04.980
See, when we're weak,

00:49:04.980 --> 00:49:06.980
we know we have to depend on Jehovah.

00:49:06.980 --> 00:49:08.980
That's really when we're the strongest.

00:49:08.980 --> 00:49:11.980
But when we think we're strong, like Peter,

00:49:11.980 --> 00:49:14.980
that's generally when we're relying on ourselves.

00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:16.980
And that's when we're the weakest.

00:49:16.980 --> 00:49:20.980
In contrast to Peter, Solomon, Jesus,

00:49:20.980 --> 00:49:23.980
never overconfidently relied on himself.

00:49:23.980 --> 00:49:25.980
And that's why he never crashed.

00:49:25.980 --> 00:49:28.980
But look at Luke chapter 22.

00:49:28.980 --> 00:49:33.980
Just one more thought here about right before his betrayal

00:49:33.980 --> 00:49:35.980
and death.

00:49:35.980 --> 00:49:39.980
See, notice how he was certainly not relying on himself,

00:49:39.980 --> 00:49:41.980
even though you could say he had billions of years

00:49:41.980 --> 00:49:44.980
of faithful service under his belt.

00:49:44.980 --> 00:49:46.980
Verse 41,

00:49:46.980 --> 00:49:49.980
He withdrew from them about a stone's throw away.

00:49:49.980 --> 00:49:53.980
He bent his knees and began to pray, saying,

00:49:53.980 --> 00:49:56.980
Father, if you want to,

00:49:56.980 --> 00:49:58.980
remove this cup from me.

00:49:58.980 --> 00:50:00.980
Nevertheless, let not my will,

00:50:00.980 --> 00:50:02.980
but yours take place.

00:50:02.980 --> 00:50:04.980
Then an angel from heaven appeared to him

00:50:04.980 --> 00:50:06.980
and strengthened him.

00:50:06.980 --> 00:50:09.980
But he was in such agony that he kept praying

00:50:09.980 --> 00:50:11.980
more earnestly,

00:50:11.980 --> 00:50:15.980
and his sweat became as drops of blood falling to the ground.

00:50:15.980 --> 00:50:17.980
Now just recently, I noticed that,

00:50:17.980 --> 00:50:19.980
and thought about this point,

00:50:19.980 --> 00:50:22.980
that even after the angel strengthened him,

00:50:22.980 --> 00:50:24.980
he didn't say, well, I've been strengthened.

00:50:24.980 --> 00:50:26.980
Now I'm good to go.

00:50:26.980 --> 00:50:29.980
No, he prayed even more intently.

00:50:29.980 --> 00:50:33.980
Truly the opposite of overconfidence.

00:50:33.980 --> 00:50:35.980
So there we have three cautions.

00:50:35.980 --> 00:50:38.980
Never overconfidently think we can take unauthorized

00:50:38.980 --> 00:50:42.980
liberties in Jehovah's organization.

00:50:42.980 --> 00:50:46.980
Number two, never overconfidently presume

00:50:46.980 --> 00:50:49.980
on Jehovah's mercy.

00:50:49.980 --> 00:50:54.980
And number three, never overconfidently rely on ourselves.

00:50:54.980 --> 00:50:56.980
Now if we observe these cautions,

00:50:56.980 --> 00:51:01.980
we'll never join the camp of the stupid ones

00:51:01.980 --> 00:51:05.980
who are reckless and overconfident.

